Wanting to spend less time indoors with a gadget and more time outdoors in nature is the dream. 
 — James Baraz

One result of being bullied is fear. When we start to avoid our own capabilities, we lose the ability to dream; and when we accept the fear of failure then we begin to accept the notion that who we are is not good enough, that we are worthless.

One of the biggest challenges to break free from the fear of failure is changing the way we live. We have to change our environment and invite new experiences. But we insiders stubbornly trust our toxic environment that keeps killing our soul.

You have everything you need to create big value in your life, your unique message given to you just as it was given to Thomas Edison, Abraham Lincoln and Oprah Winfrey.

It would take many lifetimes to realize that purposeful living starts with deliberate practice, making sure you have something important to say and are certain that it will transform lives. We belong to those rare breeds who can hold that intense vision.

In a life meant to be lived at a high level of creative expression, we find that we are able to play a meaningful role in the lives of others. We have an experience and a story to reveal.

Make a daily determination to identify one big fear in your life and practice tolerance for whatever
